actions.comment:
This is expected behavior on WASM. The Skia font manager in WASM only has access to fonts bundled into the binary (Noto Mono by default) — it cannot reach browser or system fonts from the sandbox.

Here's the recommended workaround: load fonts explicitly using `SKTypeface.FromStream()` or `SKTypeface.FromData()`:

```csharp
// Option 1: Embedded resource
using var stream = typeof(MyApp).Assembly
    .GetManifestResourceStream("MyApp.Fonts.Tahoma.ttf");
var typeface = SKTypeface.FromStream(stream);

// Option 2: Fetch from server (enables browser caching)
var fontBytes = await httpClient.GetByteArrayAsync("/fonts/Tahoma.ttf");
using var data = SKData.CreateCopy(fontBytes);
var typeface = SKTypeface.FromData(data);
```

Both `FromStream` and `FromData` can return null if the font data is invalid — add a null check before use. For best performance, load fonts once at startup and register them as a singleton service rather than reloading on each paint call.

This limitation applies to all WASM-based apps because Emscripten's sandbox doesn't expose the host font system.
